title: Wright, Richard
description[1]: These documents were compiled by Professor William J. Maxwell for his 2015 book, F.B. Eyes: How J. Edgar Hoover’s Ghostreaders Framed African American Literature. F.B.Eyes exposes the Bureau's intimate policing of five decades of African American poems, plays, essays, and novels. For more information, consult:
description[2]: Maxwell, William. F.B. Eyes: How J. Edgar Hoover’s Ghostreaders Framed African American Literature. Princeton University Press, 2015. ISBNs: 9780691130200, 9780691173412, 0691130205, 0691173419. OCLC Number(s): 903648825, 899031064. World Cat Record: https://worldcat.org/en/title/899031064
